benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/catalog/plan - Retrieve plan for a given subscription and date

covered: Valid Request: Success paths when both, only subscriptionId, or only requestedDate are provided, plus boundary-date behavior; correct plan resolved when applicable (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC13).
Query Parameters: Broad coverage of combinations and validation, including both parameters invalid and ignoring extra params (TC05–TC08, TC14).
Error Handling: 404 for non-existent subscription, 400 for malformed UUID/date, and dependency outage (503) covered; data-integrity conflict scenario included (TC07, TC05–TC06, TC10, TC12).
Empty/No Data: Empty database and no-match behaviors are exercised (TC11, TC03).
Security: Input hardening via SQL injection and XSS attempts (TC17, TC18).
Non-functional: Performance under normal and concurrent load, plus regression and backward-compatibility checks (TC15–TC16, TC19–TC20).
Scope note: Pagination is not applicable to this single-object endpoint and is reasonably omitted.
gaps: Ambiguous assertions: Several scenarios allow multiple outcomes (e.g., TC03, TC04, TC11, TC12 use “200 or … depending on implementation”), which weakens acceptance criteria and test value.
Response headers: No explicit checks for Content-Type: application/json per spec, nor Accept/content-negotiation behavior.
Response schema: No strict validation against the Plan schema (#/definitions/Plan) to ensure required fields and correct values (e.g., name, product, priceList, billingPeriod, phases).
Caching behavior: No tests for ETag/Last-Modified/Cache-Control or conditional GET (If-None-Match -> 304).
Rate limiting/throttling: No tests for 429 Too Many Requests and Retry-After when limits are exceeded.
Missing case: subscriptionId is valid but requestedDate falls outside any effective plan window for that subscription (expected behavior not asserted).
Authorization depth: No 403 Forbidden test for authenticated-but-unauthorized access (if RBAC/tenancy applies).
Date robustness: No tests for timezone/leap-day edge cases or rejection of date-time strings with timezone when only date is allowed.
recommendations: Make outcomes deterministic: agree on expected results for “omitted parameters,” “empty DB,” and “data integrity conflict” paths; replace “200 or …” with a single, clear expectation per scenario.
Add header assertions: verify Content-Type: application/json and content-negotiation via Accept; validate standard error body shape (code/message).
Add schema validation: assert the response conforms to the Plan definition (#/definitions/Plan), including required fields and value correctness.
Add caching tests: verify ETag/Cache-Control presence; send If-None-Match to assert 304 Not Modified behavior.
Add rate-limiting tests: burst requests to trigger 429 and assert Retry-After semantics.
Cover “no active plan at requestedDate” for a given subscriptionId with a clear expected status/body (e.g., 404 Not Found or documented default).
Extend date edge-case coverage: leap day (e.g., 2024-02-29), timezone boundary behavior, and rejection of date-time with timezone offsets.
Add 403 Forbidden scenario if RBAC/tenant scoping is enforced.
Optionally add stability/idempotence check: repeated GET with same inputs returns identical body and consistent headers, aligning with cacheability signals.
